<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <meta name="description" content="404 - Page not found">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="header-content">
                <div>
                    <h1>🌍 Countries API</h1>
                    <div class="subtitle">Comprehensive country data at your fingertips</div>
                </div>
                <nav>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="/">🏠 Home</a></li>
                        <li><a href="/docs">📚 API Docs</a></li>
                        <li><a href="/api/v1/countries">🔗 API</a></li>
                        <li><a href="/location">📍 Location</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </nav>
            </div>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <div class="error-page">
    <div class="error-code">404</div>
    <div class="error-message">
        Oops! The page you're looking for doesn't exist.
    </div>
    <p style="color: var(--comment); margin-bottom: 30px; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
        The country or page you requested could not be found. This might be because:
    </p>
    
    <div style="background-color: var(--current-line); padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 600px; text-align: left;">
        <ul style="color: var(--foreground); list-style: none; padding: 0;">
            <li style="margin: 10px 0;">🔍 The country code doesn't exist</li>
            <li style="margin: 10px 0;">🌍 The URL was typed incorrectly</li>
            <li style="margin: 10px 0;">📄 The page has been moved or deleted</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 40px;">
        <a href="/" class="btn">🏠 Back to Home</a>
        <a href="/api/v1/countries" class="btn btn-secondary">🔍 Browse All Countries</a>
    </div>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 30px; font-size: 0.9em; color: var(--comment);">
        <p>Need help? Check out our <a href="/docs" style="color: var(--cyan);">API documentation</a></p>
    </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer style="margin-top: 60px; text-align: center; padding: 20px; color: var(--comment); border-top: 1px solid var(--current-line);">
        <p>Countries API v1.0.0 | Built with Express.js and EJS | Dracula Theme</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>